modules.description: This module provides functions to retrieve the current time as a POSIX clock value in days and picoseconds since the epoch, query the local time zone offset in seconds, and determine the clock's period in days and picoseconds. It works with integer and 64-bit integer types to represent time values with picosecond precision. It is used for precise timekeeping in MirageOS unikernels, particularly for applications requiring synchronization with external time sources like NTP.

This module provides a monotonic clock interface for MirageOS, returning time values in nanoseconds. It includes operations to retrieve the elapsed time since an arbitrary starting point and the clock's period, if available. Useful for profiling and timing-sensitive applications where consistent time measurements are critical.
